age 81, Rock & Roll Hall of Famer Buddy Guy continues his untouchable legacy. He's influenced rock titans like Jimi Hendrix, Eric Clapton and Stevie Ray Vaughan, he's a pioneer of Chicago's fabled West Side sound, not to mention a living link to the city's halcyon days of electric blues. Guy's redefined guitar playing and he has a Presidential National Medal of Arts to show for his lifelong licks.
